  <div class="column_holder">
    <h1>
      <img alt="JOBS" src="/images/headers/pf_heading/dynamicimage.aspx?text=JOBS" />
    </h1>
    <div class="column_heading">
      <span id="ctl00_ContentPlaceHolder1_lblTop"><p>GRIN is constantly looking for talented people. All available positions are listed below. Apply via the form or by e-mail.  If you are interested in a position that isn&rsquo;t listed, please send your CV via e-mail to jobs@grin.se.</p></span></div>
    <div class="column_sep">
      <img src="img/jobs/jobs_open_sep.png" alt="Open positions" /></div>
    
    
      <div class="column_content">
        <h1>
          <img alt="Tuesday 03 February 2009" src="/images/headers/pf_small/dynamicimage.aspx?text=Tuesday 03 February 2009" />
        </h1>
        <h2>
          <img alt="Tools Programmer" src="/images/headers/pf_heading/dynamicimage.aspx?text=Tools Programmer" />
        </h2>
        <p>
          <span id="ctl00_ContentPlaceHolder1_lblJobText"><p>We have an opening to join the Grin core team in Stockholm, to help with further development of our tools pipeline.&nbsp;<br />
<br />
<strong>Day to day work includes<br />
</strong>- Working closely with artists and designers while designing new tools and user-interfaces<br />
- Supporting and extending existing core systems to cope with new requirements<br />
- Identifying studio-wide issues to improve workflow across multiple disciplines<br />
<br />
You will work closely together with artists as well as our engine department to ensure that we maintain a bleeding-edge tools pipeline.<br />
<br />
<strong>Requirements</strong><br />
- Excellent object-oriented programming and debugging skills<br />
- Solid experience with one or more dynamic programming languages (Ex. Python / Ruby / Lua)<br />
- Motivated and able to work without close supervision<br />
- Good problem-solving and communication skills<br />
- Good user-interface design skills<br />
- Previous experience with one or more GUI frameworks (Ex. wxWidgets / GTK / QT / WinForms)<br />
<br />
<strong>Pluses<br />
</strong>- Good C and C++ skills<br />
- Experience with several popular content-creation packages (Ex. Maya / Max / Photoshop / Cubase / Final Cut)<br />
- Ability to quickly grasp new technical concepts and programming languages<br />
- Prior experience with games or application programming<br />
<br />
Apply via <a href="mailto:job@grin.se">job@grin.se</a>.</p></span></p>
      </div>
      <div class="column_nav">
        <span class="column_nav_cat">Contact</span>
        <p>
          Please send your application through the online form below, or by regular mail to
          our physical adress. If you prefer to send your application by email click
          <a href="&#109;&#97;&#105;&#108;&#116;&#111;&#58;&#106;&#111;&#98;&#64;&#103;&#114;&#105;&#110;&#46;&#115;&#101;">here</a>.</p>
      </div>
